commit.message:
Use new `memory_stats` call; use pandas for formatting (#11)

* Removes obsolete 'function' field

* Support 'with LineProfiler(func) as prof' syntax

* Swaps to more detailed memory statistics and swaps to storing raw data

* Swaps to using hashes of code objects. Risks a collision, but having an ordering makes pandas happy

* Swaps to using pandas to do summarization and formatting

* Cleanup

* Fixes extension.py to work with the new setup

* Columns are now referenced with dot syntax

* Only byte-formats byte-columns

* Adds HTML rendering

* Adds passing of column names from the extension

* Left aligns headers

* Blanks nan cells

* Takes maxes over repeated lines; whoops

* Adds a note on the problem with resetting memory stats

* Makes codes private

* Fixes stats for the first line of a function

* Makes _trace_callback private

* Accumulates stats over inner functions

* Restores file-streaming functionality

* Restores print_func_stats functionality

* Restores profile_every functionality

* Adds prettier colors

* Adds pandas as a dep

* Restores profile_every export

* Adds reference to CUDA column names

* Swaps column/func arg order

* Reorders util imports

* Reorders line_profiler imports

* Swaps refine for a more literate function name

* Uses more literate loop variables

* Adds comments explaining record accumulation

* 'No data' warning goes to specified stream

* Fixes print_func_stats call in profile

* Renames raw to raw_records

* Fixes rich display with a hack for now

* Improves columnname error handling

* Adds test dependencies

* Gets text-or-HTML output working

* Adds a comment about using hash(code)

* Replaces 'prev' with 'prev_record_idx'

* Replaces 'bytecols' with 'byte_cols'

* Lots of minor PR review resolutions

* Removes an accidental copy-pasted varname. Whoops

* Reorders imports

* Adds docstrings

* Adds a test of the display mechanism

* qualname -> qual_name

* code_info -> code_infos

* Drops Python 2.7 from travis

* Adds some comments

* Minor fix

* Improves text formatting

* Removes format strings so Python 3.5 will work

* Wraps the stats reset so as to not break Travis

* Gets the IPython extension working again

* Gets Travis to use an old pandas version on 3.5

* Shortens some excessively long lines

* Fixes subsetting by function and adds a global profiler reset

* Adds back in the groupby.max I dropped somewhere

* Updates the readme

* Fixes header left-alignment in text output

* Updates the ipynb

* Adds explicit torch 1.4 dependency

* Moves IPython into install_requires

* Swaps reset_global_line_profiler for clear_global_line_profiler

* Disposes of print_func_stats

* Subs map for list comp

* Swaps noun-function names for verb-function-names

commit.message:
Add imports and function invocations to sample code (#6)

* Add imports and function invocations to sample code

Copying and pasting the existing samples either fails due to import errors, or empty profile results if the function decorated with `@profile` isn't invoked. The samples have been updated so they can all be copy and pasted and run to produce the same results listed in the README

* Add future to requirements.txt to fix failing travis build

See https://travis-ci.com/github/Stonesjtu/pytorch_memlab/jobs/299780365 for the corresponding failing job log
Ref: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/27495752/no-module-named-builtins
